What's the Best Tech Field to Learn, and Get Involved In?
text:
My background is a smart buildings engineer. I've always followed the latest tech from a far, enjoying trying to learn a bit, here, and there.

Now, I'm wondering if I wanted a career change, would it be possible, and what would be the most advantageous to get into? Here are some thoughts, so obviously in vogue right now, others could be viable, maybe some not worth it at all.

What are your thoughts?

Full stack engineering UX design Big data engineering AI something Bitcoin lightning projects Network engineering Etc?

Is there some need to know skills as we move into these unprecedented, and in some cases, worrying times?

Is it even possible to change if your in your mid thirties?

text:
Unfortunately, this was a bit to long to fit into HN's submission text field:

https://drive.proton.me/urls/HDA5M1MJEC#JcyAWGpy9PXl

It's 6 pages consisting of explanations/examples of logic/code to arrive at the conclusions.

It also just occurred that the "ID" part turns into "13", as in what will be aired in "Best Moments Of" re-broadcasts on TV next Monday, the 13th.

It would especially be appreciated if someone was knowledgeable enough to write a program figuring out the probability of all this being coincidental.

Anyway, should you care to amuse yourself with "something different", again, the document is 6 pages (1 of which is mostly images).

For anyone who downloaded it in and took the time to read it, thank you in advance for your time and consideration.

Cannot open Atom on macOS
text:
I can no longer open Atom (text editor) on macOS. I am receiving three prompts simultaneously whenever I attempt to:

1. "“Atom” will damage your computer. You should move it to the Trash." Options (Move to Trash, Cancel) *Report malware to Apple to protect other users

2. The application "Atom" can't be opened.

3. Atom quit unexpectedly

I understand the application has been deprecated a while ago so I figured the it must have something to do with how it was signed. But I have not updated it in who knows how long so I don't exactly care. Even if the keys to sign it have been revoked (which is what I have gathered through cursory web searches), for me to not be able to run the damn app on my own machine is pretty infuriating.

This is basically the last straw and I'll be installing Asahi later today. I don't need Apple playing nanny for me.
